op align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fenobleu@themagicianstower>Fenobleu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#333333>(10/23/02 9:09:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=450.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Mage Known Bug List?</span><hr size=1> Would it make sense to create a sticky or separate forum for known bugs that affect the mage class?  The purpose would be to provide a point source for bug reports with recommended community solutions in a single place that VI dev folks could come and see.  <br>
<br>
I suspect to make this work the Mage Known Bug List would have to be a Whine-Free-Zone (WFZ?) where only non-controversial bugs (e.g., bolt graphic missing) would be listed.<br>
<br>
It would probably have to be closely moderated to weed out superflous information and provide the kind of succinct detail useful to members of the dev team.  <br>
<br>
I know that individuals can and do report bugs as they come up, but a single comprehensive list benefitting from the insights of the Mage community at large seems to me to be a an effective way of communicating to the powers that be.<br>
<br>
Fenobleu Wayfarer<br>
40th level Mage, Brell Serilis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1302<br> <font color=#333333>(10/23/02 9:40:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=450.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sebminas.com/eq/baby.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mage Known Bug List?</span><hr size=1> i like this idea alot, bump <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=artulyn1>Artulyn1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#333333>(10/23/02 11:32:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=450.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Mage Known Bug List?</span><hr size=1> I have noticed one rather strange bug that happens when I cast a rain spell and then sit down right afterwards. When the damage from the next wave gets reported, my toon stands up, yet the SIT/STAND button remains on STAND. It took me a while to notice how my perspective kept changing then I took a 3rd person view to confirm it.<br>
