<br>
Similiar to how pets poof if summoned to an invalid location (i.e. inside a wall or object), eyes summoned in such locations cause the eye to spawn in a random part of the zone (guess I will get lynched for mentioning this one, but it's a BUG). While kinda fun, it's seldom useful and pretty benign.<br>
<br>
In the arena, and perhaps all other PvP areas as well, having cancel magic cast on your pet instantly destroys it. This is very unfair to pet classes, and magicians especially who get much of their offense and defense from their pet.<br>
<br>
Another arena/pvp problem. Hitting your pet with a damage spell can kill it instantly, even if the spell should not have done enough damage to kill it. Haven't tested this with rains, bolts do it if the pet winds up between you and your target. Like the above problem, this is not terribly fair to the magician. No doubt the pet should take damage if it's caught in the way, but it should not just instantly die.<br>
<br>
If you have Servant of Ro up, it will take pet commands, but your normal pet becomes uncontrollable (only the servant responds to commands). Someone reported having the opposite of this problem, pet would accept commands, but the servant would not. <br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
